Task: make `editor_sdf` update runtime SDF uniforms for numeric/property edits instead of refreshing the whole shader

Scope
- Identify which `editor_sdf` property edits currently go through full JSON reapply and shader refresh.
- Route easily alterable runtime values such as float and vector properties through direct `se_sdf` runtime setters when possible.
- Keep shape/topology edits and any changes that alter shader structure on the existing full JSON reload path.
- Preserve the JSON document as source of truth so save/load still writes the latest state.
- Keep the implementation local to `editor_sdf` unless a clear shared engine API gap is discovered.

Implementation checklist
- Inspect `editor_sdf_apply_command(...)` and classify each property into:
  - runtime-uniform update only
  - requires full `se_sdf_from_json(...)`
- Inspect `include/se_sdf.h` and `src/se_sdf.c` for setters covering:
  - transform
  - operation amount
  - shading colors/scalars
  - shadow scalars
  - point/directional light position/color/direction/radius
  - noise parameters
- Understand how `editor_sdf` item ids map to actual runtime SDF/light/noise handles.
- Add local helpers to resolve the selected JSON item to the corresponding runtime handle.
- Update command application so numeric/vector edits:
  - mutate JSON
  - apply direct runtime setter(s)
  - avoid full scene reload/recompile
- Keep structural edits such as shape type changes, descriptor type changes, child layout changes, and raw matrix fallback on the full reload path if needed.
- Add or extend autotest coverage to prove runtime-edit paths succeed.
- Build and run headless autotest.

Validation checklist
- `./build.sh editor_sdf`
- `timeout 25s env SE_TERMINAL_RENDER=1 SE_TERMINAL_HIDE_WINDOW=1 ./bin/editor_sdf --autotest`

